And ultimately, wouldn't this be even more "modern", even clearer? --<p><pre><code>    my $file_path = Path::Class::dir("some_path")->file("file_name");
    my $fh = $file_path->openw();
    $fh->print("my line\n");
    $fh->close();

</code></pre>
Or for reading the whole file quickly, instead of the @var = <FILE> idiom --<p><pre><code>    my @var = $file_path->slurp();</code></pre>
